LAND
  List your land units in a human-readable table.

SYNTAX
  land [<uid-spec>]
  lnd  [<uid-spec>]

DESCRIPTION
  Displays a table of land units you own.  With no argument shows
  all your land units.

  Column meanings:
    lnd#           - land unit uid
    land unit type - name of unit type (infantry, armor, etc.)
    x,y            - current location (relative to your capital)
    ar             - army letter (~ means not assigned to an army)
    eff            - efficiency 0-100%.  Builds up over time in any
                     owned sector, but only at full speed in a
                     headquarters or fortress -- everywhere else
                     it's a third the rate
    civ            - civilians carried
    mil            - military carried
    uw             - uncompensated workers carried
    fd             - food carried
    mob            - mobility points
    tech           - tech level the unit was built at

EXAMPLE
  land *                     all your land units
  lnd 0                      land unit number 0 only
  lnd 0-5                    land units 0 through 5

